tr: the head of a religious order
in an abbey the prior is next below the abbot

partsOfSpeech.dec: amb- 两 + ass- 做,代理做 + -ad- + -or 人或物

data.enText: happening or existing before sth else or before a particular time
Although not essential, some prior knowledge of statistics is desirable.
data.chText: 统计学的知识虽非必要，但最好是学过一点。

data.enText: This information must not be disclosed without prior written consent .
data.chText: 未事先征得书面许可，此消息不得泄露。

data.enText: Please give us prior notice if you need an evening meal.
data.chText: 需用晚餐者，请预先通知我们。

data.enText: She will be unable to attend because of a prior engagement .
data.chText: 因事先有别的安排，她将不能出席。

data.enText: already existing and therefore more important
data.chText: 优先的；占先的；较重要的

data.enText: They have a prior claim to the property.
data.chText: 他们有权优先获得该处房产。

data.enText: during the week prior to the meeting
a person who is in charge of a group of monks or nuns living in a priory
(in an abbey ) a person next in rank below an abbot or abbess

means: （中世纪佛罗伦萨及其他意大利共和国的）最高执政官

ex.enText: She has a child from a previous marriage.
ex.chText: 她前一次婚姻有一个孩子。

ex.enText: He discovered that he had met his new colleague before on three previous occasions.
ex.chText: 他发现他以前见过他的新同事3次。

synonyms.bx: 指在当下所提及的事件、时间等之前发生或存在的，通常作定语。

ex.enText: The foregoing conclusion is based on the following data.
ex.chText: 上述结论是根据以下数据得出的。

synonyms.bx: 指事物在讲述、文章等中刚刚提到的，常作定语。

ex.enText: He has a great interest in books about the former president.
ex.chText: 他对和那位前总统有关的书十分感兴趣。

ex.enText: His income has been reduced to half its former amount due to the economic depression.
ex.chText: 由于经济萧条，他的收入已减少到以前的一半。

synonyms.bx: 指曾有过某种职务或地位的，也可指发生或存在于过去的。

ex.enText: The examples in the preceding chapter are used again later.
ex.chText: 上一章的例子后面又再次被使用。

ex.enText: Their plan of seeing a movie together on Friday failed because they had a quarrel on the preceding day.
ex.chText: 他们周五一起看电影的计划泡汤了，因为他们在前一天吵了一架。

synonyms.bx: 指在所提时间、地点或部分之前发生或出现的。

ex.enText: The discussion requires prior knowledge of the subject.
ex.chText: 本次讨论要求事先了解该主题的相关知识。

ex.enText: No employee can be recruited without the prior approval of the manager.
ex.chText: 事先未征得经理的同意不可以招收任何员工。

synonyms.bx: 较正式用词，多指先于另一事物或某一时间前存在或安排的。

example.ex: He claimed he had no prior knowledge of the protest...
example.tran: 他声称自己事先并不知道这次抗议的事。

example.ex: The Constitution requires the president to seek the prior approval of Congress for military action...
example.tran: 宪法规定总统在采取军事行动之前必须获得国会同意。

example.ex: For the prior year, they reported net income of $1.1 million.
example.tran: 他们公布上一年度纯收入为110万美元。

value.def: You use prior to indicate that something has already happened, or must happen, before another event takes place.

example.ex: The firm I wanted to use had prior commitments.
example.tran: 我想选用的这家公司已有约在先。

value.def: A prior claim or duty is more important than other claims or duties and needs to be dealt with first.
value.tran: （所有权、责任）更重要的，优先的

value.def: A prior is a monk who is in charge of a priory or a monk who is the second most important person in a monastery.
value.tran: 小修道院院长；大修道院副院长

example.ex: Prior to his Japan trip, he went to New York...
example.tran: 在去日本之前，他去了纽约。

example.ex: A man seen hanging around the area prior to the shooting could have been involved.
example.tran: 在枪杀案发生之前，有人目睹一位男子在这附近游荡，该男子可能与此案有关。

value.def: If something happens prior to a particular time or event, it happens before that time or event.

trans: 现有技术；在先技术；已有技术；先前技术；先有技术
前概率；验前概率；先验概率；事前概率；事前机率
